A woman was shot during a road rage incident in Old City early Sunday morning, officials said.

At 2:46 a.m., a woman shot a 45-year-old woman in the arm and chest outside in the 100 block of Chestnut Street.

Medics took the victim to a local hospital, where she was listed in extremely critical condition, according to a statement from the PPD.

Officers took the suspect into custody and recovered the weapon she used.

[CBS Philadelphia reported](https://www.cbsnews.com/philadelphia/news/chestnut-street-old-city-road-rage-incident-shooting-philadelphia-police/) the suspect said she acted in self-defense.

nib.text:
A woman shot and critically injured a security guard after the South Street Fest in Washington Square Saturday night, officials said.

According to a statement from the PPD, at 10:46 p.m., several dirt bikes and ATVs were driving eastbound in the 700 block of South Street.

A woman in a dark-colored three-wheeled Slingshot motorcycle got into a fight with an employee of a vendor on the block, [CBS Philadelphia reported](https://www.cbsnews.com/philadelphia/news/shooting-south-street-atv-driver-philadelphia-police/).

Several security guards came over and broke up the fight; the woman returned to her vehicle.

The driver then shot one of the security guards, a 40-year-old man, in the leg and stomach.

Medics took him to a local hospital, where he remains in critical condition.

No arrests have been made. The PPD's Special Investigation Group has taken over the investigation.
